This paper deals with unsupervised partitioning problems, which are commonly studied in machine learning and computer vision. The paper specifically focuses on partitioning problems based on Euclidean distortions, which are commonly used in clustering, image segmentation, video segmentation, and change-point detection problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also deals with structured prediction problems, which are studied in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
